SUMMARY:John Primer & the Real Deal Blues Band
DESCRIPTION:The Brown County Playhouse in Nashville\, Indiana\, welcomes blues icons John Primer & The Real Deal Blues Band with special guests Paul Holdman and Gordon Bonham. \nAs a young man\, guitarist\, vocalist\, and bandleader John Primer learned Chicago blues with the masters. Primer performed regularly with legends such as Muddy Waters\, Willie Dixon\, and was a long-term band leader for Magic Slim & The Teardrops. Primer is one of the few truly-authentic Chicago bluesmen touring and recording today. He was inducted into the Blues Hall of Fame in 2023. \nPrimer’s long list of honors and accolades speak to his experience and reputation for engaging a live audience\, including: Three-time Grammy® Award nominee; Blues Artist of the Year — Living Blues critic’s poll award; Traditional Blues Artist of the Year — Blues Music Award; Lifetime Achievement Award\, Live Album of the Year\, and Traditional Blues Album of the Year — Blues Blast Awards \nBUY TICKETS\n\n \n \n \nBUY TICKETS
URL:https://browncountyplayhouse.org/event/john-primer-2026/
LOCATION:Brown County Playhouse\, 70 S. Van Buren St\, Nashville\, IN\, 47448\, United States
CATEGORIES:Blues,Clasic Rock,Country,Jazz,Live Shows,Music
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://browncountyplayhouse.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026-JohnPrimer_web_event.jpg
END:VEVENT
